<title>USA: HSBC Americas Capital Trust sets cap securities.</title>
<headline>HSBC Americas Capital Trust sets cap securities.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>The following debt issue from HSBC Americas Capital Trust II was priced on Thursday via the 144A private placement market, according to market sources.</p>
<p>The deal was jointly underwritten by HSBC Capital Markets and Lehman Brothers, they said.</p>
<p>BORROWER HSBC AMERICAS CAPITAL TRUST II</p>
<p>AMT $200 MLN	  COUPON 8.375	MATURITY  05/15/27</p>
<p>TYPE CAP SECURITIES ISS PRICE 100.00  FIRST PAY DATE</p>
<p>LAST MOODY'S  A3    YIELD  8.375	PAY FREQ  NA</p>
<p>LAST S&amp;P  BBB-PLUS  SPREAD 142 BP     CALLABLE  10</p>
<p>((--U.S. Corporate Bond Unit, 212 859-1675))</p>
